

* ste_Buffer
  handles text editing and undo

  ste doesn't really use ste_Buffers since they don't come with cursors
reasoning for this:
  other applications might want to use ste_Buffer, it wouldn't make any sense to have mutliple cursors, vi-keys or custom configurations for GUI text boxes, however, it would very much make sense to have those in a text editor, so ste_BufferWrapper handles that.
  @todo it might be a good idea to externalize ste_Buffer onto a library and rename ste_BufferWrapper to ste_Buffer, as those names make more sense.

* ste_BufferWrapper
  wraps ste_Buffer, handles cursors
* ste_Window
  selects a ste_Buffer
  handles font size, which font
